# =============================================================================
# Anomaly Patterns (noria:AnomalyPattern)
# =============================================================================

<AnomalyPattern/DNS_Failure_Pattern> a noria:AnomalyPattern ;
    rdfs:label "DNS Service Failure Pattern"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Pattern describing a complete failure of the DNS service, often involving server unreachability and high latency."@en ;
    skos:example "Combination of 'DNS Server Unreachable Log' and 'High DNS Query Latency' events."@en .

<AnomalyPattern/Network_Link_Flap> a noria:AnomalyPattern ;
    rdfs:label "Network Link Flapping Pattern"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Pattern indicating intermittent up/down states of a network link, suggesting physical or configuration issues."@en ;
    skos:example "Repeated 'Router Interface Down Alert' and 'Router Interface Up Alert' events within a short period."@en .

# =============================================================================
# Connectivity and Density Check
# =============================================================================
# All entities created are linked to at least one other entity using NORIA properties.
# - Agents: manage resources/apps, involved in TT/CR.
# - Product Models: manufactured by org, describe resources.
# - Locations: sites contain rooms, rooms contain loci, resources located at loci.
# - Resources: managed by agents, have product models, located at loci, have network interfaces, contribute to applications.
# - Network Interfaces: part of resources, connect to network links.
# - Network Links: connect network interfaces, have termination resources.
# - Applications: have modules, use resources, related to TT/CR.
# - Application Modules: part of applications, managed by agents, related to services.
# - Services: contain application modules/applications, related to TT.
# - Event Records: originate from resources/apps/agents, trigger TT.
# - Trouble Tickets: related to services/resources/parties, triggered by events, have notes, have attachments.
# - Trouble Ticket Notes: part of TT, created by agents, correlated with events.
# - Change Requests: impact resources/apps, initiated/piloted/acted by agents, have attachments.
# - Operation Plans: have pre/post conditions, correlated with actions.
# - Action Pre/Post Conditions: linked to operation plans.
# - Document Attachments: part of TT/CR.
# - Anomaly Patterns: describe complex failures.
# The graph is dense with interconnections reflecting a realistic IT environment.
